    "discriminators": [
     "A four-stroke firing order is a periodic impulse train: at idle roughly 12-30 firings per second, which puts a strong peak in the onset autocorrelation AND a harmonic comb whose fundamental is the firing frequency. On a steady idle even beats_per_minute can fire.",
     "Against MOTORS-ELECTRIC: combustion is much noisier and much more low-band, and it has that periodic impulse train. An electric motor is a clean tone with NO impulse train - onset_periodicity is the discriminator.",
     "Against MOTORS-TURBINE: a turbine is a smooth high-frequency whine with no discrete firing events.",
     "Non-vehicle engines only - generators, compressors, isolated engine recordings. If it is mounted in something that drives, it belongs in VEHICLES, and only text knows."
    ],
