    "discriminators": [
     "Any electric motor: a steady, strongly harmonic whine or hum, usually with a commutator or slot-passing overtone series. Stationary, high sustain, and with NO periodic impulse train - the absence of a firing order is what separates it from MOTORS-COMBUSTION.",
     "Against MOTORS-SERVO: a servo is short, discrete and start-stop, and it sweeps in pitch as it seeks position. This is a steady continuous run.",
     "Against MOTORS-TURBINE: a turbine sits far higher in frequency and sweeps on spool-up. See also TOOLS-POWER, which is the same motor plus a cutting load."
